The paper deals with the capacity of artificial neural networks, which is a fundamental topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper uses information theory concepts such as Shannon's communication model to derive upper bounds on the capacity of neural networks. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are the most likely categories. Additionally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are also relevant categories as they deal with neural networks and their behavior. Finally, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with a fundamental aspect of AI.
